  "prompt": "Is the activity of money laundering prohibited?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is prohibited in most countries around the world. It is a serious criminal offense that involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or bank accounts to make it appear legal. Governments and financial institutions have implemented strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to detect and prevent such activities.\n\nIn many jurisdictions, money laundering can result in significant legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal prosecution\n2. Substantial financial penalties\n3. Imprisonment\n4. Asset seizure\n5. Professional sanctions\n\nFinancial institutions are typically required to implement robust compliance programs to identify and report suspicious transactions that might indicate money laundering.",
